<article{{attributes.addClass('full-content-module')}}>

	{# Top Meta Bar: Breadcrumbs and Social Icons #}
	<div class="full-content-module__top-meta">
		<div class="full-content-module__breadcrumbs">
			<a href="/">Home</a>
			<span class="full-content-module__breadcrumbs-divider">›</span>
			<span class="full-content-module__breadcrumbs-current">Legal</span>
		</div>

		<div class="full-content-module__social-share full-content-module__social-share--plain">
			<a href="https://web.com" aria-label="Convene NGO Website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				{{ _self.icon_svg('link') }}
			</a>
			<a href="https://linkedin.com" aria-label="LinkedIn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				{{ _self.icon_svg('linkedin') }}
			</a>
			<a href="https://twitter.com" aria-label="X (Twitter)" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				{{ _self.icon_svg('x') }}
			</a>
			<a href="https://facebook.com" aria-label="Facebook" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
				{{ _self.icon_svg('facebook') }}
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="full-content-module__body text-block">
		<h1>Introduction</h1>

		<p>Welcome to Convene ("we," "our," or "us"). As a non-governmental organization committed to driving positive social impact, transparency and trust are at the core of everything we do. This document outlines our Privacy Policy, Terms and Conditions, and our compliance with international non-profit regulations.</p>

		<p>By interacting with our platform, registering for our events, or contributing to our charitable initiatives, you agree to the ethical standards and operational policies defined herein. We value the privacy of our donors, volunteers, and beneficiaries and are fully compliant with standard global frameworks including the GDPR.</p>

		<figure>
			{% include 'canvas:image' with {
				src: figure_image_url|default('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1540575467063-178a50c2df87?w=800&q=80'),
				alt: 'Community gathering and collaboration',
				loading: 'lazy',
				class: '',
			} only %}
			<figcaption>Convene NGO Community Impact Gathering</figcaption>
		</figure>

		<p class="lead">Our commitment is to ensure that your personal information is processed lawfully, fairly, and with absolute transparency for specific, explicit, and legitimate developmental purposes.</p>

		<p>We actively gather data strictly for the purposes of facilitating international aid events, processing tax-deductible contributions, and maintaining clear communication with our generous donor network. We do not sell, trade, or unfairly distribute personal supporter information to third-party marketing entities under any circumstances. Event attendance metrics and anonymous survey results are only utilized to measure the operational effectiveness of our campaigns.</p>

		<blockquote>
			"Transparency is the foundation of trust. We are dedicated to ensuring every supporter understands precisely how their actions and contributions empower our global missions."
		</blockquote>

		<p>If you are registering for one of our regional conferences or digital seminars, please note that photography and video recordings may take place for archival and grant-reporting purposes. You retain the full right to opt-out of media inclusion during the on-site registration process by speaking with one of our event coordinators.</p>

		<h2>Conclusion & Contact Rights</h2>

		<p>Under applicable international data protection laws, including the European Union's GDPR, you have the right to request access to the personal data we hold about you. You may also request corrections, restriction of processing, or full deletion of your records from our donor management systems at any time.</p>

		<p>To exercise any of these rights, express concerns regarding our terms of representation, or to request our annual financial transparency reports, please reach out to our legal and compliance team at <strong>legal@convene-ngo.org</strong>.</p>

		<p>We reserve the right to modify these operational and privacy terms periodically to align with evolving international non-profit regulations. Notice of significant changes will be communicated proactively via our official newsletter and across our verified social media channels.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="full-content-module__bottom-meta">
		<div class="full-content-module__share-this">
			<span class="share-label">Share this</span>
			<div class="full-content-module__social-share full-content-module__social-share--circle">
				<a href="https://web.com" aria-label="Convene NGO Website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					{{ _self.icon_svg('link') }}
				</a>
				<a href="https://linkedin.com" aria-label="LinkedIn" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					{{ _self.icon_svg('linkedin') }}
				</a>
				<a href="https://x.com" aria-label="X (Twitter)" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					{{ _self.icon_svg('x') }}
				</a>
				<a href="https://facebook.com" aria-label="Facebook" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					{{ _self.icon_svg('facebook') }}
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="full-content-module__tags">
			<span class="tag">Legal</span>
			<span class="tag">Privacy</span>
			<span class="tag">User Testing</span>
			<span class="tag">Test Data</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="full-content-module__event-team">
		<div class="event-team-avatar event-team-avatar--placeholder">
			<svg width="48" height="48" viewbox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
				<rect width="48" height="48" fill="url(#pattern0_14_1401)"/>
				<defs>
					<pattern id="pattern0_14_1401" patterncontentunits="objectBoundingBox" width="1" height="1">
						<use xlink:href="#image0_14_1401" transform="scale(0.0208333)"/>
					</pattern>
					<image id="image0_14_1401" width="48" height="48" preserveaspectratio="none" xlink:href="data:image/png;base64,"/>
				</defs>
			</svg>
		</div>

		<div class="event-team-name">Jane Doe</div>

		<div class="event-team-role">Head of Events</div>
	</div>
</article>
